Here is the PlantUML code for the given requirement:

title Campaign State Machine Diagram

state "Idle" as Idle
Idle : entry/No campaign assigned
Idle : do/Remain in same state
Idle : exit/Assign manager and staff / Start campaign

state "Start Campaign" as StartCampaign
StartCampaign : entry/Manager and staff assigned
StartCampaign : do/Start campaign
StartCampaign : exit/Activate campaign

state "Activate Campaign" as ActivateCampaign
ActivateCampaign : entry/Campaign activated
ActivateCampaign : do/Prepare adverts
ActivateCampaign : exit/Approve adverts

state "Prepare Adverts" as PrepareAdverts
PrepareAdverts : entry/Adverts prepared
PrepareAdverts : do/Approve adverts
PrepareAdverts : exit/Schedule adverts

state "Schedule Adverts" as ScheduleAdverts
ScheduleAdverts : entry/Adverts scheduled
ScheduleAdverts : do/Run adverts
ScheduleAdverts : exit/Adjust campaign

state "Adjust Campaign" as AdjustCampaign
AdjustCampaign : entry/Campaign adjusted
AdjustCampaign : do/Run adverts
AdjustCampaign : exit/Complete campaign

state "Complete Campaign" as CompleteCampaign
CompleteCampaign : entry/Campaign completed
CompleteCampaign : do/Prepare final statement
CompleteCampaign : exit/Pay campaign

state "Pay Campaign" as PayCampaign
PayCampaign : entry/Pay campaign
PayCampaign : do/Handle payment
PayCampaign : exit/Archive campaign

state "Archive Campaign" as ArchiveCampaign
ArchiveCampaign : entry/Campaign archived
ArchiveCampaign : do/Release staff and managers
ArchiveCampaign : exit/End

state "Refund Campaign" as RefundCampaign
RefundCampaign : entry/Refund campaign
RefundCampaign : do/Generate refund
RefundCampaign : exit/Wait for balance

state "Wait for Balance" as WaitForBalance
WaitForBalance : entry/Wait for balance
WaitForBalance : do/Wait for balance
WaitForBalance : exit/Mark campaign as paid

state "Mark Campaign as Paid" as MarkCampaignAsPaid
MarkCampaignAsPaid : entry/Mark campaign as paid
MarkCampaignAsPaid : do/Mark campaign as paid
MarkCampaignAsPaid : exit/End

